						<summary>

						<p>This inscription is also much damaged. It is dated in Śaka 1467, Viśvāvasu (A.D. 1546-47) in the reign of the same king (<hi rend="bold">Sadāśiva</hi>) and refers to Pūttalaippaṭṭu as situated in Veṅgaḷappaṟṟu-śīrmai a southern division of Tiruvēṅgaḍak-kōṭṭam in Peruṅgoṇḍai-(Penukoṇḍa)-rājyam. It seems to record a gift of land to the temple of Perumāḷ in the village.</p>						

						</summary>
